        <pb pNum="227"/>
        <poem xml:id="p-9">
            <title>Buddy</title>
            
                <stanza>
                    <lb num="1"/>That kid's my buddy,
                    <lb num="2"/>still and yet
                    <lb num="3"/>I don't see him much.
                    <lb num="4"/>He works downtown for Twelve a week.
                    <lb num="5"/>Has to give his mother Ten-
                    <lb num="6"/>she says he can have
                    <lb num="7"/>the other Two
                    <lb num="8"/>to pay his carfare, buy a suit,
                    <lb num="9"/>coat, shoes,
                    <lb num="10"/>anything he wants out of it.
                </stanza>
            
        </poem>
        <poem xml:id="p-10">
            <title>Juke Box Love Song</title>
            
                <stanza>
                    <lb num="1"/>I could take the Harlem night
                    <lb num="2"/>and wrap around you,
                    <lb num="3"/>Take the neon lights and make a crown,
                    <lb num="4"/>Take the Lenox Avenue busses,
                    <lb num="5"/>Taxis, subways,
                    <lb num="6"/>And for your love song tone their rumble down.
                    <lb num="7"/>Take Harlem's heartbeat,
                    <lb num="8"/>Make a drumbeat,
                    <lb num="9"/>Put it on a record, let it whirl,
                    <lb num="10"/>And while we listen to it play,
                    <lb num="11"/>Dance with you till day-
                    <lb num="12"/>Dance with you, my sweet brown Harlem girl.
                </stanza>
            
        </poem>
        <pb pNum="228"/>
        <poem xml:id="p-11">
            <title>Ultimatum</title>
            
                <stanza>
                    <lb num="1"/>Baby, how come you can't see me
                    <lb num="2"/>when I'm paying your bills
                    <lb num="3"/>each and every week?
                </stanza>
                <stanza>
                    <lb num="4"/>If you got somebody else,
                    <lb num="5"/>tell me-
                    <lb num="6"/>else I'll cut you off
                    <lb num="7"/>without your rent,
                    <lb num="8"/>I mean
                    <lb num="9"/>without a cent.
                </stanza>
            
        </poem>
